@node Introduction

  @{b}- Introduction -@{ub}

This is version 1.60 of AnArchiver, which is a Gui for handling archives.
It allows you to Extract files (by using xadmaster) from various types
of archives, and you can Add, Delete and Test files to/in LhA, LZX and
Zip archives. All this can be done in a nice and easy way by using a GUI.

It's not one of those simple programs that only can act upon ALL files
in the source dir (adding), or ALL files in the archive (extracting). 
No this is the real thing, where you actually can select any amount of
files to add, extract or delete to/from/in the archive.



   @{b}- Why I made it -@{ub}

I decided to make AnArchiver because I was getting a bit tired of having
to create archives in Shell, and I wanted an easier way of doing it.
So I searched for a long time to find a good Archiver program, but the few
ones I found was either of the simple type mentioned above or it was some
old grey and boring Topaz 8 ridden kind of thing that was best used with
a Highres screenmode.

In other words, I wanted a program that had a lot of features and was made
for a "modern" OS, but since I could not find one that suited my needs,
I decided to make one myself.

The strange thing is that while there are plenty of Gui's for extracting
files from archives, only a few of them supports compressing.



   @{b}- Why it is called AnArchiver -@{ub}

I'm sure that some of you are wondering about the reason why this program
is called AnArchiver, so here is the explenation:

When I started developing AnArchiver, I had some problems with coming up
with a name for it. I was thinking about calling it "Pakker", but since I
found this name to be a bit dull, I dropped this idea. Then I was thinking
about simply calling it "Archiver", but nope, that name was already taken
by another program. I really had some problems with finding a name that was
not already used by other programs. But I finally came up with the name
"Another Archiver", which I later decided to shorten to "AnArchiver".

@endnode

